(41, 9, '2011-01-01', '0000-00-00', '專業交流 陽光家訪', '<p align="center"><strong>一月份通訊</strong></p>\r\n<p>親愛的家長：</p>\r\n<p>　　開學至今，本校師生積極進取，學生在多項的校外比賽中屢獲殊榮，學校亦獲教育局評選為資訊科技教育卓越中心，反映本校在推動創意教學及科技教學方面，成效顯著。</p>\r\n<p>　　 本校老師積極進修，9月至今學校安排多位老師參與日間進修及赴內地進行交流，包括陳美華主任、陳章華主任、盧翠儀老師、馮凱茵老師、陳遜發老師等。此外，本校趙曼娜主任獲教育局邀請，將於2011年1月至5月參與「香港教師赴內地交流協作項目」，向內地老師分享英文教學經驗，實屬難得。在老師進修期間，若時期較長，本校會安排資深教師擔任代課，不會影響學生的學習進度。</p>\r\n<p>　　為照顧學生成長需要，本校將分階段進行陽光電話及陽光家訪活動。全校老師將於12月及1月份為小六學生進行陽光家訪，讓家長有更多機會與老師面談，進一步加強家校合作，一同為孩子的成長努力！另外，本校一直保持良好的教學水平，為讓家長更了解學生的學習表現，本校於上學期及下學期舉行兩次家長觀課活動，首次活動已於12月15日順利舉行，觀課級別包括小一、小三及小五的中文、英文及數學科，下學期將安排其他級別進行公開課，詳情請留意通告。</p>\r\n<p>　　為進一步提供多元化的網上資訊，學校將於1月及2月進行網頁更新，期間新舊網頁並行，為家長及學生提供適應期。如有任何查詢，歡迎與陳章華主任聯絡。</p>\r\n<p>　　聖誕將至，隨函附上2011年年曆卡及由本校協助製作的音樂光碟作為禮物。敬祝各位聖誕快樂！新年進步！</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">校長&nbsp;&nbsp;黃靜雯　謹啟</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">2010年12月20日</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Monthly Newsletter　(December)</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">20st December , 2010</p>\r\n<p>Dear Parents/Guardians,</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Since September, our teachers have worked to motivate  students to excel in many areas.&nbsp; A  number of students have participated in award-winning in-school competitions.&nbsp; In addition the school has been selected as the Information Technology Education Center of Excellence, reflecting  the school in promoting&nbsp;creative teaching and technology skills with remarkable results.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Many of our teachers are  participating in various Mainland exchanges including: Ms. Chang Mei Wah, Mr. Chan Cheung Wah, Ms. Lo Tsui Yi, Ms. Fung Hoi Yan, and Mr. Chen Shun  Faat . In addition, Miss Chiu Man Nar also has been invited by the Education Bureau director to  participate in &quot;Hong Kong teachers to the mainland exchanges and cooperation projects&quot; from January to  May, 2011.&nbsp; Mainland and Hong Kong English teachers will share their teaching experiences with one another.  &nbsp;During this time, experienced supply teachers will continue lessons with the students so that their learning will  not be interrupted.</p>\r\n<p>　 To cater for the  developmental needs of students, the school will implement the Sunshine  telephone and home visits.&nbsp; Teachers will conduct home visits in December  and January for primary six students. The home visits will give parents  more opportunities to communicate directly with teachers to further enhance home-school relationships to foster students'' growth. In  addition, the school held lesson observations for parents on 15th  December to allow parents to have a better understanding of their child&rsquo;s  learning.&nbsp; Lesson observations were held in  P.1, P.3 and P.5 classes in Chinese, English and Mathematics lessons. In  the next term,  we will arrange demonstration lessons at other levels.&nbsp; Please watch for more information.</p>\r\n<p>　Also,  to further provide a wide  range of online information, the school will hold information sessions on website updates for parents, which will be held in January and February.</p>\r\n<p>　 For enquiries, please contact Mr. Chan Cheung Wah.</p>\r\n<p>　 The attached pocket sized calendar and the music CD  are Christmas gifts for you. I wish you all a merry Christmas and a happy New Year!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">Sincerely,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: right;">Ms.  Wong Ching Man, Principal</p>', '', 'http://', 1, '', 2010, '100', '', '0000-00-00', NULL),
