ont-size:11.0pt;\r\nfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";\r\nmso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0pt;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->  </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Dear Parents,</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN" style="font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">The P.1-3 Games Day was successfully held on 23<sup>rd</sup> March. One of the most valuable lessons learned through activities is for students to always do their best. The students fully embodied the spirit of Kei Tsz Games Day by actively participating, challenging themselves, having good teamwork and being consistent. Our school has always been concerned with the importance of the health of students and hold regular health promotion activities including the election of ten healthy foods, spinal care activities, Sport ACT Award and inter-class balanced lunch competitions. In addition, swimming and rock climbing have been included in the regular P.E. curriculum. Archery lessons have also been available to P.4-6 students to allow them to experience the fun of sports.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN" style="font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Easter holiday is coming. Finally we can be relieved from our work. It is a great time to have some rest and enjoy a few days with our family. During this joyful season, I wonder, do we really understand the meaning of Easter?</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN" style="font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Before or during Easter holiday, there are Easter eggs and rabbit decorations in many shops. People in western countries generally believe that there are two lives in eggs. The first life of an egg is &lsquo;newborn&rsquo;, the second life of an egg is &lsquo;reborn&rsquo;. To be reborn also represents Jesus&rsquo; resurrection. The white rabbits represent peace, love and joy. These decorations remind us that Jesus Christ is the Saviour of all men. He is the one who can free us from our sin and help us to be reborn. &ldquo;For what I received I passed on to you as of first importance: that Christ died for our sins according to the Scriptures, that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day according to the Scriptures&rdquo; (1 Corinthians 15:3-4, NIV). &nbsp;Jesus died because he wants to free us from our sins. Jesus was buried but raised from death three days later. These events show that God loves us. He gives us hope and lets us have peace and joy.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN" style="font-family: &quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">I hope that Easter is not only a break from school, but also a great opportunity for us to understand the real meaning of Easter and the joy and the grace we have through the resurrection of Jesus. Then, we can receive God&rsquo;s grace and appreciate his sacrifice for us.&nbsp; </span><span lang="EN" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">During the Easter holiday, P.4 students will join a two-day Gospel Camp, so that they understand the meaning of the Gospel, what it means to have faith in Jesus, self-reflect and learn how to have an enriched life. In addition, teachers will conduct P.3 home visits with parents to exchange ideas and have a better understanding of student development needs. Finally, I pray for good health and happiness for you!</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="right" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\r\nauto;text-align:right;mso-pagination:widow-orphan" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Sincerely, </span></span></p>\r\n<p align="right" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\r\nauto;text-align:right;mso-pagination:widow-orphan" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Wong Ching Man</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="right" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\r\nauto;text-align:right;mso-pagination:widow-orphan" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Principal</span></span></p>', '', 'http://', 1, '', 2011, '31', '', '0000-00-00', NULL);
