riority="32" SemiHidden="false"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Intense Reference" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="33" SemiHidden="false"\r\nUnhideWhenUsed="false" QFormat="true" Name="Book Title" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="37" Name="Bibliography" />\r\n<w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="39" QFormat="true" Name="TOC Heading" />\r\n</w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n/* Style Definitions */\r\ntable.MsoNormalTable\r\n{mso-style-name:表格內文;\r\nmso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\nmso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\nmso-style-noshow:yes;\r\nmso-style-priority:99;\r\nmso-style-qformat:yes;\r\nmso-style-parent:"";\r\nmso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\nmso-para-margin:0cm;\r\nmso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\nfont-size:12.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";\r\nmso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-font-kerning:1.0pt;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">30<sup>th</sup> April, 2012</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Dear Parents,</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Our school always puts emphasis on the character and academic development of students. We respect individual uniqueness through curriculum planning and different types of activities. We work with parents to help students cultivate a holistic life. During the Easter holiday, all teachers participated in Neuro-Linguistic Programming (NLP) Practitioner training courses to understand how positive thinking from a psychological point can impact students&rsquo; growth, and further understand how effective communication and communication skills can be beneficial to students. In addition, the teachers and I visited all primary three and pre-primary one families to understand the students'' backgrounds and developmental needs. During the home visits, many parents expressed their appreciation of the caring culture and also praised the profound dedication to education established in the school. I take this opportunity to extend my extreme gratitude to the staff team that has worked hard on this!</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Parents should have received the test results from your child. Some students have satisfactory results and some may still need to put more effort into their studies.&nbsp; Regardless of the scores, the most important thing for us is to develop children''s positive attitude towards learning. The school has begun to regulate the content of the examination papers to correlate with the new policies of secondary schools, like the Fine-tuning of Medium of Instruction for Secondary Schools and Hong Kong Diploma of Secondary Education to fully reflect the academic performance of students and prepare for future studies.&nbsp; As the Classic of Rites said, &ldquo;When he learns, one knows his own deficiencies; when he teaches, he knows the difficulties of learning. After he knows his deficiencies, one is able to turn round and examine himself; after he knows the difficulties, he is able to stimulate himself to effort.&rdquo;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Many students hope to get good results in order to enter schools with good reputation and have better career opportunities in the future. However, if learning is equivalent to a shortcut to fame and fortune, examinations will only create more self-centered and selfish people. Let us work together to let our children to know the true meaning of examinations so that they can be beneficial in their lives.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">(1) have the courage to face challenges</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Students must go through the trials of examinations. Students can learn how to persevere to overcome difficulties, and finally reach their targets. This perseverance will help students face future challenges and to complete the mission God entrusted to them.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">(2) develop thinking skills</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Examinations a</span><span lang="EN-GB" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">re a good way to train students to understand, analyze, express themselves and organize ide</span><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">as. They are required to answer questions in a short period of time, which helps them develop communication and problem solving skills and enhances them to have confidence to face alone the difficulties.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">(3) improve learning attitude</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Examinations are used to understand students&rsquo; progress. Parents and teachers can use students&rsquo; results to help them improve their learning methods and attitudes. We not only need to guide them to recognize a learning focus, but also encourage them to become loyal. In the Bible, we learn that we should be faithful stewards and use our talents to respond to our love for God and others.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">I hope that parents and the school can work together to train children to have good character and learn actively. In addition, the school has received a notice from the Education Bureau that we are going to have four classes in primary one in the coming academic year. May all the glory go to our God in heaven. Finally, I pray for your health and happiness!</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="right" class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\r\nauto;text-align:right;mso-pagination:widow-orphan"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Sincerely, </span></span></p>\r\n<p align="right" class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\r\nauto;text-align:right;mso-pagination:widow-orphan"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Wong Ching Man</span></span></p>\r\n<p align="right" class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\r\nauto;text-align:right;mso-pagination:widow-orphan"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span lang="EN-US" style="font-family: &quot;新細明體&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;">Principal</span></span></p>', '', 'http://', 1, '', 2011, '31', '', '0000-00-00', NULL);
